rlUInt8_t txGainTempLut [RL_TX_CNT][RL_MAX_NUM_OF_TEMP10_RANGES+1U]
 Gain code for Tx0/1/2
Byte0: TX gain code for temperature < -30 deg C
Byte1: TX gain code for temperature [-30, -20) deg C
Byte2: TX gain code for temperature [-20, -10) deg C
Byte3: TX gain code for temperature [-10, 0) deg C
Byte4: TX gain code for temperature [0, 10) deg C
Byte5: TX gain code for temperature [10, 20) deg C
Byte6: TX gain code for temperature [20, 30) deg C
Byte7: TX gain code for temperature [30, 40) deg C
Byte8: TX gain code for temperature [40, 50) deg C
Byte9: TX gain code for temperature [50, 60) deg C
Byte10: TX gain code for temperature [60, 70) deg C
Byte11: TX gain code for temperature [70, 80) deg C
Byte12: TX gain code for temperature [80, 90) deg C
Byte13: TX gain code for temperature [90, 100) deg C
Byte14: TX gain code for temperature [100, 110) deg C
Byte15: TX gain code for temperature [110, 120) deg C
Byte16: TX gain code for temperature [120, 130) deg C
Byte17: TX gain code for temperature [130, 140) deg C
Byte18: TX gain code for temperature >= 140 deg C
Byte19: RESERVED. Set it to 0x00
Each byte is encoded as follows
Bits Definition
[5:0] STG_CODE
Higher values for higher gain
[7:6] RESERVED
.
